This World Motorcycle Day, we celebrate the sheer range of experience that Triumph motorcycles brings you.

Starting right from the adventure seekers, to the connoisseurs of motorcycling who appreciate modern technology shrouded in  timeless form, saddled up on their modern classics, or even the ones who celebrate sheer power and like to live on the edge, Triumph has something for every motorcycle enthusiast around the world.

Different journeys. Distinct sensibilities. One name that brings them all together.

Happy World Motorcycle Day

latestPosts.caption:
Legendary motorcycles inspired by a legendary daredevil.​

Behold the Triumph Rocket 3 Evel Knievel Limited Editions, which capture the fearless spirit of Evel Knievel with a
unique design and performance that command attention.​

Evel Knievel, the greatest daredevil of all time, made history riding Triumph motorcycles. This edition honours Knievel's most iconic feat - the 1967 Caesar’s Palace jump, where he soared 141 feet over the famous fountains on a Triumph Bonneville, a moment that made him a global sensation.​

The Rocket 3 R Evel Knievel Limited Edition is limited to only 250 units worldwide. With only 3 units having made their way to India, it is one of the rarest motorcycles to own.​

Every owner will receive an exclusive, collector's edition hardback book, specially commissioned by Triumph to tell
the remarkable story of Evel Knievel and his iconic connection with the brand. Written by renowned author and Knievel
expert Stuart Barker, each book will be individually numbered and signed by Triumph CEO, Nick Bloor​

​
[Triumph Motorcycles, Triumph India, Rocket 3R, Evel Knievel, Legend]
